	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p rend="align(center)"><placeName>N York</placeName>&#44; <date>Nov 2. 5621&#47;1860</date>.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Dear Sir&#8212;</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)"><sic>Inclosed</sic> the continuation<lb/> of the &#8220;Declaration of Independence.&#8221;  I<lb/> thought the portion sent to you at first&#44;<lb/> was enough for <hi rend="underline">two</hi> weeks&#44; as I<lb/> wish to spin out the publication till<lb/> <date>Chanukah</date>.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Your correspondent &#8220;<hi rend="underline"><persName>Counsellor</persName></hi>&#8221; deals<lb/> in contemptible duplicity.  He says&#58; &#8220;<persName>Rev.<lb/> Dr Fishel</persName> &#38;c &#38;c.&#8221; &#40;page 189&#44; col. 3&#41; What<lb/> is the truth&#63;  104 votes were cast&#44; of<lb/> these <persName>F.</persName> received 53&#44; that is to say&#44; he<lb/> was reelected by a majority of two<lb/> votes.  If he had yet one spark of<lb/> pride and principle left in him&#44; he<lb/> would have respectfully declined&#59; but<lb/> no&#44; even because half of the congregati<lb/>on do not want him&#44; he will take<lb/> <hi rend="underline">their</hi> money and they <hi rend="underline">must</hi> listen to<lb/> him&#44; or he will receive <del>their</del> insult<lb/> offered to him by their leaving the Syna&#45;</p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p>gogue when he ascends the pulpit.  Be&#45;<lb/>sides&#44; he has been reelected only for one<lb/> year.  Oh&#33; He is a man of principle<lb/> &#38; character.  Counsel your correspondent<lb/> <persName><sic>counsellor</sic></persName> to be more candid &#38; truth&#45;<lb/>ful in future.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Why have you not a word of<lb/> censure for the attempted vandalism of <persName>Dr<lb/> Sachs</persName> of <placeName>Berlin</placeName>&#63;  To me&#44; that man is<lb/> henceforth more hateful &#38; obnoxious than<lb/> even <persName>Cardinal Antonelli</persName>.  Why have<lb/> you not yet said a word about the<lb/> fanatic acts of the Orthodox of <placeName>Amster&#45;<lb/>dam</placeName>.  Yet&#44; you scold&#44; because &#8220;rich Re&#45;<lb/>formers&#8221; will not suffer themselves to be<lb/> brow&#45;beaten into hypocrisy by ortho&#45;<lb/>dox fanatics &#38; hypocrites.  I am open<lb/> with you&#58; I sometimes get perplexed<lb/> in my respect for the <hi rend="underline">Orthodox</hi>&#59;<lb/> for withholding truth borders very<lb/> closely upon uttering untruth&#33;&#8221;</p>
				<p>I was not present at the Banquet&#59;<lb/> but I <hi rend="underline">know</hi> that the &#8220;rich reformers&#8221; re&#45;</p>
			<pb n="3"/>
				<p>mained uncovered during &#8220;<hi rend="underline">Benschen</hi>&#8221;&#44;<lb/> which awful sacrilegious act did not<lb/> present the Hospital from making<lb/> &#36;14.000 by the operation.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">By the bye&#59; The Keneseth Israel<lb/> of <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName> <del>of</del> <hi rend="underline">begged</hi> me again<lb/> after <add>&#63;</add> to become their minister&#44; but<lb/> I declined again.  No doubt&#44; this my<lb/> seeming hardheartedness induced<lb/> them to accompany the two silver goblets<lb/> which they sent me with rather stiff &#38;<lb/> cold resolutions&#44; and to do the thing<lb/> so very privately&#33;&#33; &#8220;<hi rend="underline"><add>&#63;</add></hi>&#33;&#8221;</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">There is general dissatisfaction among<lb/> the Portuguese&#59; this Synagogue is a<lb/> <hi rend="underline">complete failure</hi>&#59; they think already<lb/> of abandoning it.  The &#8220;rich reformers&#8221;<lb/> will build a &#8220;<hi rend="underline">Temple</hi>&#8221; that will throw<lb/> all Synagogues here into darkness.<lb/>  Concerning the <placeName>Norfolk Street</placeName> Synagogue&#44;<lb/> I can say&#58; Put it down as a <hi rend="underline">Re</hi>&#45;<lb/><hi rend="underline">form</hi> concern&#59; <persName>Dr Gruenebaum</persName> will<lb/> manage it&#59; he comes out in his true</p>
			<pb n="4"/>
				<p>having been elected as Reformer&#59;<lb/> and let me tell you into a secret&#58;<lb/> a third&#44; <hi rend="underline">American</hi>&#45;Reform&#45;Congregati&#45;<lb/>on will soon spring into existence&#33;&#33;</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">God speed it <add>Hebrew</add></p>
			<p rend="indent(3)">Yours&#44; as ever&#44;</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)"><persName role="author">M Mayer</persName></p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">Please send me one or<lb/> two more copies of the<lb/> paper containing the<lb/> &#8220;Declaration of Indep.&#8221;<lb/> as I wish to send one<lb/> to <persName>Stein</persName>.</p>
		</body>
